<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - OIL PICK-UP TUBE
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OIL PICK-UP TUBE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With pulley damper removed, remove the oil pick-up tube as follows: (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050733">7.33</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ). (Rear sump tube shown).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the two (2) retaining bolts at the front cover.</para>
                    <figure id="ef1050732" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2379" filename="../figeg2/EG2379.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.32.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Pulley Damper</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Universal Puller</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050733" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2388" filename="../figeg2/EG2388.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.33.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Oil Pick-Up Tube</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Crankcase</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Front Cover</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. Oil Pick-Up Tube Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Support oil pick-up tube and remove retaining bolt at support bracket (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e105_155.xml" xrefid="ef1050734">7.34</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the pick-up tube and gasket. Discard gasket.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
